Ceska Sporitelna AS, the Czech unit
of  Erste Bank AG (EBS) , said first-quarter net income rose 17.2
percent as provisions for bad loans declined.  Net income for three months ended March 31 was 4.46 billion
koruna ($238 million) compared with 3.8 billion koruna a year
ago, the Prague-based lender said in an e-mailed statement. Net
interest income rose 5.1 percent to 7.84 billion koruna.  To contact the reporter on this story:
